WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

2
00:02:10.798 --> 00:02:13.467
Ser Ryam was a strong Lord Commander

3
00:02:13.551 --> 00:02:15.094
of the Kingsguard.

4
00:02:16.387 --> 00:02:18.347
But he was ill for some time.

5
00:02:18.431 --> 00:02:20.057
He passed in peace. I hope.

6
00:02:20.141 --> 00:02:21.100
Yes. Your Grace.

7
00:02:21.183 --> 00:02:22.435
He was found to have passed

8
00:02:22.518 --> 00:02:24.353
gently in his sleep.

9
00:02:24.437 --> 00:02:27.773
His remains are being prepared
by the Silent Sisters.

10
00:02:27.857 --> 00:02:31.193
The succeeding Lord Commander.
Ser Harrold.

11
00:02:31.277 --> 00:02:35.573
would like to make haste in finding
Ser Ryam's replacement on the Kingsguard.

12
00:02:35.656 --> 00:02:37.658
Your Grace. My lords.

13
00:02:38.326 --> 00:02:41.204
The Kingsguard must soon be restored
to its full complement of seven.

14
00:02:42.622 --> 00:02:44.040
With the help of the Hand.

15
00:02:44.123 --> 00:02:46.626
I've invited a number of
fine candidates to court.

16
00:02:46.709 --> 00:02:48.586
All have passed fair trials.

17
00:02:52.840 --> 00:02:54.759
Four ships have now been lost.

18
00:02:54.842 --> 00:02:56.177
The last one was flying my banner.

19
00:02:57.219 --> 00:02:59.180
The Stepstones have now
grown into a conflagration.

20
00:02:59.263 --> 00:03:01.724
yet you sit here
and dither about court business.

21
00:03:01.807 --> 00:03:03.976
If you've something
to discuss. Lord Corlys--

22
00:03:04.060 --> 00:03:05.853
I want to know what is to be done

23
00:03:05.937 --> 00:03:08.022
about my ships and my men.

24
00:03:08.105 --> 00:03:09.315
The Crown will compensate you

25
00:03:09.398 --> 00:03:11.525
for your ship and crew.
and make an offering

26
00:03:11.609 --> 00:03:14.695
-to the men's families.
-I don't want compensation.

27
00:03:16.822 --> 00:03:19.200
I want to seize the Stepstones by force

28
00:03:19.283 --> 00:03:20.743
and burn out this Crabfeeder.

29
00:03:20.826 --> 00:03:23.746
I am not prepared to start
a war with the Free Cities.

30
00:03:23.829 --> 00:03:26.540
These pirates are not the Free Cities.

31
00:03:26.624 --> 00:03:29.710
Who do you think provides them
with their ships and tender?

32
00:03:30.169 --> 00:03:32.004
In all of its history. my lord.

33
00:03:32.088 --> 00:03:33.965
the Seven Kingdoms have never entered

34
00:03:34.048 --> 00:03:35.758
open war with the Free Cities.

35
00:03:35.841 --> 00:03:37.468
Were that to happen.

36
00:03:37.551 --> 00:03:40.346
the losses would be incalculable.

37
00:03:44.350 --> 00:03:47.269
What reason does
the Crabfeeder have to fear us?

38
00:03:49.981 --> 00:03:52.441
The King's own brother has been allowed
to seize Dragonstone

39
00:03:52.525 --> 00:03:55.528
and fortify it with an army
of his gold cloaks.

40
00:03:55.611 --> 00:03:58.197
Daemon has squatted there
for over half a year

41
00:03:58.280 --> 00:04:00.241
without even a protest from The Crown.

42
00:04:00.324 --> 00:04:03.119
I'll caution you. Lord Corlys.

43
00:04:03.202 --> 00:04:06.706
a seat at the King's table
does not make you his equal.

44
00:04:10.209 --> 00:04:11.627
I have acted. Corlys.

45
00:04:12.962 --> 00:04:15.965
I've sent envoys to Pentos and Volantis

46
00:04:16.048 --> 00:04:17.883
to see if we might find common cause.

47
00:04:18.718 --> 00:04:21.053
Ships and men are at the ready.

48
00:04:21.929 --> 00:04:25.266
The Stepstones will be settled in time.

49
00:04:25.975 --> 00:04:28.144
You have dragonriders. father.

50
00:04:34.692 --> 00:04:35.776
Send us.

51
00:04:40.698 --> 00:04:43.951
It isn't that simple. Rhaenyra.

52
00:04:44.035 --> 00:04:45.578
It would be a show of force.

53
00:04:46.203 --> 00:04:48.164
At least the Princess has a plan.

54
00:04:52.001 --> 00:04:54.545
-I only meant that we should at least--
-Perhaps.

55
00:04:54.628 --> 00:04:58.799
there's some better use
for the Princess's talents. Your Grace.

56
00:05:01.552 --> 00:05:03.763
Why don't you take the Princess
to see about the new

57
00:05:03.846 --> 00:05:05.473
Kingsguard posting. Lord Commander?

58
00:05:07.349 --> 00:05:08.809
A fine idea. Your Grace.

59
00:05:10.895 --> 00:05:13.481
This knight will protect you as well.

60
00:05:13.564 --> 00:05:15.107
You should choose.

61
00:05:35.753 --> 00:05:37.797
Ser Desmond Caron.

62
00:05:37.880 --> 00:05:40.174
a fine knight. Princess.

63
00:05:40.257 --> 00:05:42.176
Step forward. Ser Desmond.

64
00:05:44.595 --> 00:05:46.180
Son of Ser Royce Caron.

65
00:05:46.263 --> 00:05:48.808
Ser Desmond has proved strong and steady

66
00:05:48.891 --> 00:05:51.811
in both the tourney lists and without.

67
00:05:51.894 --> 00:05:54.730
While traveling through the Kingswood
on his way to King's Landing.

68
00:05:54.814 --> 00:05:57.775
Ser Desmond recently brought
a would-be poacher

69
00:05:57.858 --> 00:05:58.984
to justice.

70
00:06:09.787 --> 00:06:13.249
You might thank him
for his leal service. Princess.

71
00:06:13.332 --> 00:06:16.460
We thank you for your loyal
service to The Crown. ser.

72
00:06:28.139 --> 00:06:30.057
Ser Rymun Mallister.

73
00:06:32.476 --> 00:06:35.396
Son of Lord Lymond Mallister of Seagard.

74
00:06:35.479 --> 00:06:37.523
Winner of the melee at Cider Hall.

75
00:06:38.023 --> 00:06:40.818
He was the last mounted
of three-and-twenty knights.

76
00:06:40.901 --> 00:06:42.945
Ser Rymun was knighted at eight-and-ten.

77
00:06:43.028 --> 00:06:45.114
Do any of these knights
have combat experience?

78
00:06:46.574 --> 00:06:48.284
Beyond capturing poachers.

79
00:06:56.500 --> 00:06:58.419
Ser Criston Cole.

80
00:07:04.466 --> 00:07:07.386
Son of the steward
of the Lord of Blackhaven.

81
00:07:09.597 --> 00:07:11.348
Be welcome. Ser Criston.

82
00:07:13.684 --> 00:07:15.936
You saw combat in the Stormlands.

83
00:07:16.020 --> 00:07:18.189
Dornish marches. Princess.

84
00:07:18.272 --> 00:07:21.400
I fought for a year as a foot solider
against the Dornish incursions.

85
00:07:22.526 --> 00:07:24.486
Ser Arlan Dondarrion
knighted me after we razed

86
00:07:24.570 --> 00:07:26.488
two of the watchtowers along the Boneway.

87
00:07:32.203 --> 00:07:33.871
I choose Ser Criston Cole.

88
00:07:34.413 --> 00:07:37.458
Let's not be too hasty. Princess.

89
00:07:38.667 --> 00:07:41.754
There's no doubt Ser Criston
is a fine warrior.

90
00:07:41.837 --> 00:07:44.298
but houses such as Crakehall and Mallister

91
00:07:44.381 --> 00:07:46.967
are important allies of The Crown.

92
00:07:47.051 --> 00:07:49.762
Seagard. for instance.
is the realm's prime defense

93
00:07:49.845 --> 00:07:51.513
against reavers from the Iron Islands.

94
00:07:51.597 --> 00:07:53.140
Those men are tourney knights.

95
00:07:53.766 --> 00:07:56.018
My father should be defended by a man
who's known real combat.

96
00:07:58.854 --> 00:07:59.980
Should he not?

97
00:08:02.274 --> 00:08:04.109
Of course. Princess.

98
00:08:04.193 --> 00:08:06.737
Well. let us plan Ser Criston's
investiture then.

99
00:08:15.246 --> 00:08:18.165
The Valyrian capital
was built into a volcano.

100
00:08:18.249 --> 00:08:19.750
much like Dragonstone.

101
00:08:20.793 --> 00:08:23.837
And the dragonlords.
the highest of the nobility.

102
00:08:23.921 --> 00:08:26.840
lived here. at the volcanic face.

103
00:08:26.924 --> 00:08:30.094
closest to the source
of their magic and power.

104
00:08:30.177 --> 00:08:31.971
And this was the Anogrion.

105
00:08:34.139 --> 00:08:36.267
Where the bloodmages worked their craft.

106
00:08:38.936 --> 00:08:41.146
It is truly wondrous what you've built.

107
00:08:41.230 --> 00:08:42.189
Oh no.

108
00:08:43.565 --> 00:08:47.111
I only pore over the histories
and provide the plans.

109
00:08:47.194 --> 00:08:49.488
The stonemasons built the structures.

110
00:08:49.989 --> 00:08:52.866
Do you believe that Westeros
can be another Valyria. Your Grace?

111
00:08:52.950 --> 00:08:55.119
That depends.
whether you speak of the Freehold

112
00:08:55.202 --> 00:08:57.121
at its height or at its fall.

113
00:08:58.622 --> 00:09:00.291
Over a thousand dragons.

114
00:09:00.374 --> 00:09:03.294
a navy large enough to span
the seas of the world.

115
00:09:06.547 --> 00:09:09.466
The glory of Old Valyria
will never be seen again.

116
00:09:10.718 --> 00:09:12.261
Seven Hells.

117
00:09:28.152 --> 00:09:29.903
Tell me. how is Rhaenyra?

118
00:09:30.612 --> 00:09:32.281
-What do you mean?
-Well. these days.

119
00:09:32.364 --> 00:09:34.700
she doesn't say more
than a few words to me.

120
00:09:35.117 --> 00:09:37.286
I think she might find it difficult

121
00:09:38.662 --> 00:09:40.581
to discuss personal matters.

122
00:09:42.333 --> 00:09:43.542
It will take time.

123
00:09:45.753 --> 00:09:47.588
It did when I lost mine own mother.

124
00:09:53.969 --> 00:09:55.888
I wish she would approach me.

125
00:09:57.556 --> 00:09:58.807
What if you went to her?

126
00:09:59.808 --> 00:10:01.602
There are times when I would rather face

127
00:10:01.685 --> 00:10:04.730
the Black Dread himself
than mine own daughter of 15.

128
00:10:07.900 --> 00:10:10.819
I think she would open
herself to you if invited.

129
00:10:11.862 --> 00:10:15.199
You do have such an easy way about you.
Your Grace.

130
00:10:19.370 --> 00:10:22.331
You do not mention our talks to Rhaenyra.
do you?

131
00:10:24.792 --> 00:10:25.918
I just.

132
00:10:27.336 --> 00:10:29.421
I fear that she wouldn't understand them.

133
00:10:30.214 --> 00:10:31.757
No. Your Grace.

134
00:10:45.354 --> 00:10:48.065
It's only been half a year
since my mother died.

135
00:10:48.148 --> 00:10:50.150
and already they tried
to marry my father off

136
00:10:50.234 --> 00:10:52.403
and replace me as heir.

137
00:10:52.486 --> 00:10:54.530
I know those men and how they plot

138
00:10:54.613 --> 00:10:57.825
in their secret councils
when I've been sent away.

139
00:10:57.908 --> 00:11:01.453
You cannot worry at the matters
of lords and kings. Rhaenyra.

140
00:11:03.539 --> 00:11:05.457
What if your father were to remarry?

141
00:11:14.174 --> 00:11:16.093
Your father loves you.

142
00:11:22.266 --> 00:11:24.184
He chose you for his heir.

143
00:11:25.394 --> 00:11:27.938
He didn't choose me. He spurns Daemon.

144
00:11:45.581 --> 00:11:47.124
Kneel with me.

145
00:12:04.266 --> 00:12:06.810
I find this is a way to be with my mother.

146
00:12:08.604 --> 00:12:10.522
Here in the quiet of the Sept.

147
00:12:11.982 --> 00:12:13.525
I feel close to her.

148
00:12:18.906 --> 00:12:22.451
-I know it sounds foolish.
-I don't think it's foolish.

149
00:12:23.702 --> 00:12:25.621
-I don't.
-Good.

150
00:12:29.124 --> 00:12:31.043
Because I thought you might try.

151
00:12:34.463 --> 00:12:37.925
If not for me. then. perhaps for them.

152
00:13:03.492 --> 00:13:05.410
What do I say?

153
00:13:06.245 --> 00:13:07.788
Whatever you wish.

154
00:13:09.289 --> 00:13:11.208
It's only for you and the gods to know.

155
00:13:46.118 --> 00:13:49.288
I want him to see me as
more than his little girl.

156
00:13:51.957 --> 00:13:55.252
Mine own father does not know
the language of girls either.

157
00:13:59.423 --> 00:14:01.258
When I wish to talk with him.

158
00:14:02.301 --> 00:14:04.428
I know that I must make the effort.

159
00:14:08.307 --> 00:14:09.141
Thank you.

160
00:14:21.570 --> 00:14:23.447
{\an8}Your Grace.

161
00:14:23.530 --> 00:14:24.823
{\an8}I'm glad we could meet.

162
00:14:25.657 --> 00:14:27.242
I know tempers ran hot today.

163
00:14:27.326 --> 00:14:29.411
and I wanted to assure you
how much I value the bond

164
00:14:29.494 --> 00:14:31.038
between our houses.

165
00:14:31.580 --> 00:14:34.124
Rhaenys is my favorite cousin after all.

166
00:14:35.667 --> 00:14:38.629
I wish to apologize for the tenor

167
00:14:38.712 --> 00:14:41.006
at the Small Council today. Your Grace.

168
00:14:41.089 --> 00:14:42.674
It was not my intent to make offense.

169
00:14:43.967 --> 00:14:47.554
Your fleet is one of the realm's
most important assets. Lord Corlys.

170
00:14:48.221 --> 00:14:49.765
But you must understand.

171
00:14:49.848 --> 00:14:52.267
as King. it is my obligation to avoid war

172
00:14:52.351 --> 00:14:54.561
until such time it is unavoidable.

173
00:14:54.645 --> 00:14:56.772
None among us desire open war.

174
00:14:58.482 --> 00:15:00.734
Might I speak plainly. Your Grace?

175
00:15:02.152 --> 00:15:05.530
I always welcome the unfettered thoughts
of my council.

176
00:15:05.614 --> 00:15:09.951
I fear that the eyes of our enemies
are presently fixed on the Red Keep.

177
00:15:10.827 --> 00:15:12.329
The Queen has passed.

178
00:15:12.412 --> 00:15:14.498
A girl has been named
heir to the Iron Throne.

179
00:15:14.581 --> 00:15:16.458
the first in its history.

180
00:15:16.541 --> 00:15:18.085
The King's brother. so disinherited.

181
00:15:18.168 --> 00:15:20.295
has claimed the Targaryen seat
on Dragonstone

182
00:15:20.379 --> 00:15:21.922
without challenge.

183
00:15:22.964 --> 00:15:25.550
And now. a foreign power
has established a colony

184
00:15:25.634 --> 00:15:27.761
in our most critical shipping lane.

185
00:15:29.096 --> 00:15:32.599
You paint such an aspirant portrait
of my reign. Lord Corlys.

186
00:15:32.683 --> 00:15:34.601
It is an honest one. cousin.

187
00:15:35.769 --> 00:15:38.814
At the moment. The Crown is perceived
as being vulnerable.

188
00:15:39.773 --> 00:15:41.692
And a blind incursion in the Stepstones

189
00:15:41.775 --> 00:15:44.027
is the only way to demonstrate
that we are not?

190
00:15:44.111 --> 00:15:47.656
To elude a storm.
you can either sail into it.

191
00:15:47.739 --> 00:15:49.324
or around it.

192
00:15:49.408 --> 00:15:51.868
But you must never await its coming.

193
00:15:53.328 --> 00:15:56.081
Do you have a specific
course of action to propose.

194
00:15:56.164 --> 00:15:57.791
my lord?

195
00:16:00.252 --> 00:16:02.087
Join our families.

196
00:16:02.921 --> 00:16:04.548
Wed our daughter. Laena.

197
00:16:04.631 --> 00:16:07.843
Unite the two great surviving
Valyrian houses.

198
00:16:07.926 --> 00:16:11.138
With the Targaryen dragons
and the Velaryon fleet bound in blood.

199
00:16:11.221 --> 00:16:12.681
you can show the realm

200
00:16:12.764 --> 00:16:15.517
that The Crown's strongest days are ahead.

201
00:16:15.600 --> 00:16:16.685
not behind.

202
00:16:21.648 --> 00:16:23.191
I must admit.

203
00:16:23.900 --> 00:16:25.819
I haven't given marriage much thought.

204
00:16:26.611 --> 00:16:28.905
It hasn't even been half a year
since Aemma passed.

205
00:16:28.989 --> 00:16:32.534
The realm expects you to take a new wife
soon or late. Your Grace.

206
00:16:32.617 --> 00:16:35.746
to strengthen your line
and produce more heirs.

207
00:16:35.829 --> 00:16:38.957
You could not ask for
a stronger match than Laena.

208
00:17:07.027 --> 00:17:09.154
We haven't spoken much

209
00:17:11.907 --> 00:17:13.116
since.

210
00:17:16.620 --> 00:17:18.246
A regret of mine.

211
00:17:19.956 --> 00:17:23.543
We should be free to speak our minds
to one another.

212
00:17:23.627 --> 00:17:25.170
You can say whatever you'd like.

213
00:17:25.253 --> 00:17:26.963
You are the King.

214
00:17:35.180 --> 00:17:39.184
I loved your mother very much.

215
00:17:42.521 --> 00:17:43.814
As did I.

216
00:18:00.121 --> 00:18:03.291
Ser Harrold provided
a fine field of tourney knights.

217
00:18:03.375 --> 00:18:04.501
Oh?

218
00:18:05.836 --> 00:18:07.462
But in questioning them.

219
00:18:07.546 --> 00:18:10.173
I discovered that Ser Criston
was the only man among them

220
00:18:10.257 --> 00:18:12.384
with true battle experience.

221
00:18:13.218 --> 00:18:15.762
He'll make a fine
knight of the Kingsguard.

222
00:18:21.268 --> 00:18:24.855
-Today at Small Council--
-Pay it no mind.

223
00:18:24.938 --> 00:18:27.732
-I thought I might have had some insight.
-You're young.

224
00:18:28.859 --> 00:18:29.985
You will learn.

225
00:18:54.801 --> 00:18:58.346
This is our best chance
to save the digit. Your Grace.

226
00:19:00.473 --> 00:19:02.559
The maggots will remove the dead flesh

227
00:19:02.642 --> 00:19:05.187
and hopefully stop the advance of the rot.

228
00:19:11.067 --> 00:19:13.778
I held an audience earlier today

229
00:19:13.862 --> 00:19:16.031
with Lord Corlys and Princess Rhaenys.

230
00:19:16.114 --> 00:19:18.283
That was most charitable
of you. Your Grace.

231
00:19:18.366 --> 00:19:21.244
I'm sure Lord Corlys
appreciated the spirit of it.

232
00:19:21.745 --> 00:19:23.663
He proposed a marriage.

233
00:19:25.081 --> 00:19:27.334
To whom. Your Grace?

234
00:19:28.084 --> 00:19:29.628
The Lady Laena.

235
00:19:30.462 --> 00:19:32.547
To combine the strength of our houses.

236
00:19:32.631 --> 00:19:35.884
and demonstrate my reign's
strongest days are ahead.

237
00:19:35.967 --> 00:19:37.052
not behind.

238
00:19:37.135 --> 00:19:39.512
Lord Corlys has overreached. Your Grace.

239
00:19:40.347 --> 00:19:43.808
Such matters must be discussed
with the Small Council.

240
00:19:43.892 --> 00:19:46.603
That is what I'm doing. presently.

241
00:19:48.146 --> 00:19:51.691
So. what is your advice. dear Otto.

242
00:19:52.817 --> 00:19:54.361
The Lady Laena

243
00:19:55.320 --> 00:19:57.906
is young. Your Grace.

244
00:19:57.989 --> 00:20:01.201
Indeed. but the wounds
made by the Great Council

245
00:20:01.284 --> 00:20:03.203
still linger. my King.

246
00:20:03.286 --> 00:20:06.539
A match with their daughter
would go a long way towards

247
00:20:06.623 --> 00:20:08.625
sealing the breach

248
00:20:08.708 --> 00:20:11.586
and uniting the two great Valyrian houses

249
00:20:11.670 --> 00:20:15.131
would certainly signal unity
throughout the realm

250
00:20:15.215 --> 00:20:16.716
and beyond.

251
00:20:17.467 --> 00:20:19.844
The Grand Maester's reasoning is sound.

252
00:20:21.721 --> 00:20:23.515
I do fear what Rhaenyra might think.

253
00:20:23.598 --> 00:20:25.517
What does it matter. Your Grace?

254
00:20:25.600 --> 00:20:27.936
Her mother has passed.

255
00:20:28.019 --> 00:20:30.397
Her father must propagate the royal line.

256
00:20:37.487 --> 00:20:41.408
I dearly loved my own lady wife.

257
00:20:42.534 --> 00:20:45.453
The pain of her passing still haunts me.

258
00:20:47.247 --> 00:20:49.165
And to be compelled to

259
00:20:50.417 --> 00:20:52.961
replace her for duty's sake.

260
00:20:54.713 --> 00:20:56.256
You are the King.

261
00:20:57.382 --> 00:20:59.300
But I do not envy you.

262
00:21:28.204 --> 00:21:30.749
What was it like flying the Black Dread?

263
00:21:30.832 --> 00:21:33.710
{\an8}You were Balerion's last rider.

264
00:21:34.294 --> 00:21:37.464
Only for a short time before he died.

265
00:21:37.547 --> 00:21:38.590
With Balerion

266
00:21:38.673 --> 00:21:41.259
died the last memory of Valyria of Old.

267
00:21:42.260 --> 00:21:44.012
But Vhagar still lives

268
00:21:44.637 --> 00:21:46.222
somewhere.

269
00:21:46.306 --> 00:21:48.224
Bit too large for the Dragonpit.

270
00:21:48.850 --> 00:21:51.394
Some would say too large for our world.

271
00:21:52.353 --> 00:21:55.440
-Do you know where she nests?
-I'm sorry?

272
00:21:55.523 --> 00:21:57.525
Do you know where Vhagar is now?

273
00:21:57.609 --> 00:22:00.320
The Dragonkeepers believe she made home

274
00:22:00.403 --> 00:22:02.822
somewhere on the coast of the Narrow Sea.

275
00:22:02.906 --> 00:22:06.534
The workers at Spicetown report
hearing her song at times.

276
00:22:06.618 --> 00:22:08.745
They say it is a sad thing.

277
00:22:10.622 --> 00:22:12.499
I imagine even dragons get lonely.

278
00:22:17.212 --> 00:22:18.463
Your Grace.

279
00:22:19.714 --> 00:22:21.674
it would be a great honor

280
00:22:21.758 --> 00:22:25.929
to join our houses
as they were in Old Valyria.

281
00:22:26.012 --> 00:22:27.222
I would give you many children

282
00:22:27.305 --> 00:22:29.224
of pure Valyrian blood

283
00:22:29.307 --> 00:22:31.476
so that we might strengthen the royal line

284
00:22:31.559 --> 00:22:33.061
and the realm.

285
00:22:33.144 --> 00:22:35.313
Is that what your father told you to say?

286
00:22:40.401 --> 00:22:41.861
What did your mother tell you?

287
00:22:43.822 --> 00:22:46.950
That I wouldn't have to bed you
until I turned 14.

288
00:23:14.435 --> 00:23:15.854
It bothers you. does it not?

289
00:23:21.776 --> 00:23:23.319
My father is a king.

290
00:23:24.028 --> 00:23:27.282
It is his duty to take a new wife
and strengthen his line.

291
00:23:27.365 --> 00:23:28.575
I did not ask for a lesson in politics.

292
00:23:28.658 --> 00:23:30.034
I asked whether this bothers you.

293
00:23:30.118 --> 00:23:31.452
Laena is your daughter. Princess.

294
00:23:31.536 --> 00:23:33.204
Does it bother you?

295
00:23:34.497 --> 00:23:35.623
Of course. it does.

296
00:23:37.667 --> 00:23:40.712
But I understand the order of things.

297
00:23:42.505 --> 00:23:44.841
I'm not sure you do.

298
00:23:47.552 --> 00:23:50.847
If you mean to elicit some anger from me.

299
00:23:50.930 --> 00:23:53.683
you should know that
you're failing. Princess.

300
00:23:54.601 --> 00:23:56.144
Quite the opposite.

301
00:23:59.606 --> 00:24:01.232
Whether it's to my daughter
or to someone else's.

302
00:24:01.316 --> 00:24:04.235
your father will remarry sooner than late.

303
00:24:05.069 --> 00:24:07.655
His new wife will produce new heirs.

304
00:24:07.739 --> 00:24:10.617
and chances are better than not
that one of those will be male.

305
00:24:10.700 --> 00:24:13.286
And when that boy comes of age
and your father has passed.

306
00:24:13.369 --> 00:24:16.247
the men of the realm
will expect him to be heir.

307
00:24:16.331 --> 00:24:17.665
not you.

308
00:24:20.251 --> 00:24:22.170
Because that is the order of things.

309
00:24:24.589 --> 00:24:26.883
When I'm Queen. I will create a new order.

310
00:24:28.468 --> 00:24:30.595
How I wish that could be. Rhaenyra.

311
00:24:31.346 --> 00:24:33.848
But the men of the realm
already had their opportunity

312
00:24:33.932 --> 00:24:36.267
to appoint a ruling queen
at the Great Council

313
00:24:36.351 --> 00:24:37.852
and they denied it.

314
00:24:37.936 --> 00:24:40.813
They denied you. Princess Rhaenys.

315
00:24:41.814 --> 00:24:43.775
"The Queen Who Never Was."

316
00:24:44.525 --> 00:24:47.320
But they bent the knee to me
and called me heir to the throne.

317
00:24:47.403 --> 00:24:50.365
Do you remind your father's men of that
as you carry their cups?

318
00:24:54.911 --> 00:24:56.871
Here is the hard truth.

319
00:24:56.955 --> 00:25:00.124
which no one else has
the heart to tell you.

320
00:25:01.000 --> 00:25:04.671
Men would sooner put
the realm to the torch

321
00:25:04.754 --> 00:25:07.674
than see a woman ascend the Iron Throne.

322
00:25:12.553 --> 00:25:15.139
And your father is no fool.

323
00:25:28.987 --> 00:25:32.573
The Small Council is urging me to remarry.

324
00:25:34.409 --> 00:25:36.953
It seems the realm wants for a new queen.

325
00:25:42.166 --> 00:25:45.670
A good and kind queen
will give comfort to your subjects.

326
00:25:50.758 --> 00:25:54.304
Does the Small Council
have a particular lady in mind?

327
00:25:56.222 --> 00:26:00.893
Lord Corlys Velaryon has offered
the hand of his daughter.

328
00:26:00.977 --> 00:26:02.520
the Lady Laena.

329
00:26:03.646 --> 00:26:05.565
A very strong match. Your Grace.

330
00:26:07.233 --> 00:26:10.778
I must admit.
I don't know Laena very well.

331
00:26:11.654 --> 00:26:13.990
I'm sure that she is good and kind.

332
00:26:14.073 --> 00:26:17.618
and that she will enjoy your company.
as I have. Your Grace.

333
00:26:33.176 --> 00:26:34.719
I brought you something.

334
00:26:55.365 --> 00:26:57.408
I asked the stonemasons to mend it.

335
00:27:01.412 --> 00:27:03.373
This is

336
00:27:03.456 --> 00:27:06.250
a very kind gesture. Alicent.

337
00:27:10.713 --> 00:27:12.632
Very kind.

338
00:27:19.764 --> 00:27:21.599
Come.

339
00:27:24.060 --> 00:27:26.187
The Hand. Your Grace.

340
00:27:30.608 --> 00:27:33.986
Your Grace. I've called the Small Council
to an emergency session.

341
00:27:34.070 --> 00:27:34.987
Why?

342
00:27:36.406 --> 00:27:38.741
I think it best you hear it directly.

343
00:27:40.159 --> 00:27:41.285
Very well.

344
00:28:12.316 --> 00:28:15.153
-Daemon.
-The Prince left a missive.

345
00:28:15.236 --> 00:28:17.238
which I believe might explain.

346
00:28:18.364 --> 00:28:21.075
"It is the pleasure of Daemon Targaryen.

347
00:28:21.159 --> 00:28:22.952
"the Prince of Dragonstone

348
00:28:23.035 --> 00:28:26.956
"and rightful heir to the Iron Throne.

349
00:28:27.039 --> 00:28:29.792
"to announce that he is
to take a second wife

350
00:28:29.876 --> 00:28:32.795
"in the tradition of Old Valyria.

351
00:28:32.879 --> 00:28:37.967
"She is to assume the title
Lady Mysaria of Dragonstone.

352
00:28:38.050 --> 00:28:40.011
"Her Grace is with child

353
00:28:40.094 --> 00:28:45.266
"and is to have a dragon's egg
placed in the babe's cradle

354
00:28:45.349 --> 00:28:48.644
in the custom of House Targaryen."

355
00:28:48.728 --> 00:28:52.356
The Prince has invited you
to his wedding. Your Grace.

356
00:28:53.316 --> 00:28:56.569
-It is in two days' time.
-Gods be good.

357
00:28:56.652 --> 00:28:58.654
Who is Lady Mysaria?

358
00:28:58.738 --> 00:29:00.448
-We believe--
-Daemon's whore.

359
00:29:02.992 --> 00:29:06.162
-This is nothing less than sedition.
-I strongly agree. sire.

360
00:29:06.245 --> 00:29:08.372
My brother wishes to provoke me.

361
00:29:09.165 --> 00:29:11.125
To answer is to give him what he wants.

362
00:29:11.209 --> 00:29:13.503
The realm is watching. Your Grace.

363
00:29:13.586 --> 00:29:15.129
What would you have me do?

364
00:29:15.213 --> 00:29:17.131
Send him to the Wall?

365
00:29:17.757 --> 00:29:19.759
Perhaps I could put his head on a spike.

366
00:29:19.842 --> 00:29:21.719
Daemon has seized Dragonstone.

367
00:29:21.802 --> 00:29:24.555
has surrounded himself
with an army of gold cloaks.

368
00:29:24.639 --> 00:29:26.724
and has now stolen a dangerous weapon.

369
00:29:54.669 --> 00:29:56.671
Assemble a detachment. Otto.

370
00:29:57.922 --> 00:29:59.799
I will go to Dragonstone
and drag Daemon back

371
00:29:59.882 --> 00:30:02.176
-to face justice myself.
-Your Grace.

372
00:30:03.511 --> 00:30:05.721
My apologies. Your Grace.
but I cannot allow it.

373
00:30:05.805 --> 00:30:07.390
It's too dangerous.

374
00:30:07.473 --> 00:30:09.392
Daemon is without limit.

375
00:30:10.434 --> 00:30:12.520
Let me go to Dragonstone.

376
00:30:39.463 --> 00:30:41.841
You're the most comely girl at court.

377
00:30:42.800 --> 00:30:44.927
Why do you destroy yourself?

378
00:30:51.350 --> 00:30:53.477
Will you see the King tonight?

379
00:30:56.439 --> 00:30:57.773
If you wish it.

380
00:31:01.152 --> 00:31:04.113
-Good day. Ser Criston.
-My Lady.

381
00:31:04.196 --> 00:31:07.199
I've assembled 20 of your best
household guards. my Lord Hand.

382
00:31:07.283 --> 00:31:09.410
Sir Harrold will also join us.

383
00:31:13.706 --> 00:31:16.626
Please look after the Hand. Ser Criston.

384
00:32:36.706 --> 00:32:38.833
Welcome to Dragonstone. Otto.

385
00:32:41.293 --> 00:32:44.296
Your occupation of this island
is at an end.

386
00:32:45.464 --> 00:32:47.466
You're to relinquish the dragon's egg.

387
00:32:47.550 --> 00:32:49.009
disband your army.

388
00:32:49.093 --> 00:32:50.886
banish your whore.

389
00:32:52.138 --> 00:32:54.724
and leave Dragonstone
by order of His Grace.

390
00:32:54.807 --> 00:32:57.226
-King Viserys.
-Where is the King? I don't see him.

391
00:32:57.309 --> 00:33:01.105
His Grace would never lower himself
to entertain such a mummer's farce.

392
00:33:06.527 --> 00:33:08.195
Ser Crispin. wasn't it?

393
00:33:08.279 --> 00:33:09.822
Ser Criston Cole. my Prince.

394
00:33:09.905 --> 00:33:11.991
Yes. apologies. I couldn't recall.

395
00:33:12.491 --> 00:33:15.035
Perhaps my Prince recalls
when I knocked him off his horse.

396
00:33:17.288 --> 00:33:18.247
Very good.

397
00:33:18.330 --> 00:33:21.250
This is a truly pathetic show. Daemon.

398
00:33:21.333 --> 00:33:23.169
Are you so desperate
for the King's attention

399
00:33:23.252 --> 00:33:25.880
that you've resorted to skulking about
like a common cutpurse?

400
00:33:25.963 --> 00:33:28.466
I'm simply keeping with
the traditions of my house.

401
00:33:28.549 --> 00:33:30.384
the same as my brother did for his heir.

402
00:33:30.468 --> 00:33:33.345
Those traditions are for the trueborn
children of royalty.

403
00:33:33.429 --> 00:33:36.140
not for bastards fathered
on a common whore.

404
00:33:36.849 --> 00:33:38.809
Lady Mysaria is to be my wife.

405
00:33:38.893 --> 00:33:40.269
This is an abomination.

406
00:33:40.352 --> 00:33:42.188
With every breath you soil your name.

407
00:33:42.271 --> 00:33:44.064
your house. and your brother's reign.

408
00:33:44.148 --> 00:33:47.276
Our love does not know
titles and traditions.

409
00:33:48.652 --> 00:33:50.946
And what of you. men of the City Watch?

410
00:33:51.030 --> 00:33:52.531
Aiding the Prince in his treason?

411
00:33:52.615 --> 00:33:54.575
The King made me their commander.

412
00:33:54.658 --> 00:33:55.993
They are loyal to me.

413
00:33:57.077 --> 00:33:58.996
You've come for the egg.

414
00:34:00.498 --> 00:34:01.749
Here it is.

415
00:34:03.250 --> 00:34:05.127
Are you mad?

416
00:34:05.211 --> 00:34:07.963
-You'd never survive this.
-Well. happily. neither would you.

417
00:34:09.215 --> 00:34:14.094
To chose violence. here.
is to declare war against your King.

418
00:34:14.178 --> 00:34:15.304
Wonderful.

419
00:34:16.680 --> 00:34:19.892
Even if it ends in the death
of your unborn child and its mother?

420
00:34:58.931 --> 00:35:00.057
All of you.

421
00:35:00.724 --> 00:35:02.643
sheathe the fucking steel.

422
00:36:09.960 --> 00:36:13.005
-What are you doing here. Princess?
-Preventing bloodshed.

423
00:36:13.088 --> 00:36:16.091
Ser Criston. please escort
the Princess to safety.

424
00:36:16.175 --> 00:36:18.052
Take care not to startle Syrax. my lords.

425
00:36:18.802 --> 00:36:20.512
She's rather protective of me.

426
00:37:10.938 --> 00:37:12.982
I'm right here. Uncle.

427
00:37:15.150 --> 00:37:17.069
the object of your ire.

428
00:37:17.820 --> 00:37:20.698
the reason that you were disinherited.

429
00:37:20.781 --> 00:37:23.075
If you wish to be restored as heir.

430
00:37:23.158 --> 00:37:24.702
you'll need to kill me.

431
00:37:25.995 --> 00:37:27.121
So. do it.

432
00:37:28.455 --> 00:37:30.582
And be done with all this bother.

433
00:39:23.362 --> 00:39:26.198
You announced that we were to be wed?

434
00:39:27.449 --> 00:39:28.992
On the morrow.

435
00:39:30.702 --> 00:39:32.621
And that I was with child.

436
00:39:33.497 --> 00:39:35.082
Your child.

437
00:39:35.165 --> 00:39:38.418
Well. perhaps when we are wed.
we can make that true.

438
00:39:38.502 --> 00:39:42.464
I ensured long ago that I would never be
threatened by childbirth.

439
00:39:42.548 --> 00:39:45.384
Good. Children can be such
irritating creatures.

440
00:39:45.467 --> 00:39:48.053
You swore to protect me. Daemon.

441
00:39:50.264 --> 00:39:52.391
Dragonstone is quite secure.

442
00:39:54.476 --> 00:39:58.981
Until the King decides to reclaim
his ancestral seat.

443
00:39:59.064 --> 00:40:01.817
His men might not put
the Prince's head on a spike.

444
00:40:01.900 --> 00:40:04.153
but what would they do
with the common whore

445
00:40:04.236 --> 00:40:06.905
he claims he's taken to wife
and made with child?

446
00:40:06.989 --> 00:40:08.532
No one will harm you.

447
00:40:09.741 --> 00:40:14.037
I have been sold as property
more times than I care to count.

448
00:40:14.121 --> 00:40:17.541
beginning in a homeland
I can no longer recall.

449
00:40:18.834 --> 00:40:22.171
Most of my years have been spent
living in terror.

450
00:40:23.046 --> 00:40:25.048
You're safe with me. I swear it.

451
00:40:25.132 --> 00:40:26.508
You are Targaryen.

452
00:40:26.592 --> 00:40:29.761
You can afford to play
your stupid games with the King.

453
00:40:29.845 --> 00:40:31.763
but I cannot.

454
00:40:32.848 --> 00:40:37.561
I didn't come into your service
wanting gold or power

455
00:40:37.644 --> 00:40:39.771
or station.

456
00:40:39.855 --> 00:40:43.609
-I came to you to be liberated.
-Liberated.

457
00:40:46.737 --> 00:40:47.905
From what?

458
00:40:49.239 --> 00:40:50.365
Fear.

459
00:41:17.643 --> 00:41:19.311
No. please. Lord Lyonel.

460
00:41:25.275 --> 00:41:28.070
I have come looking for
an unencumbered opinion.

461
00:41:28.153 --> 00:41:30.614
That's all I would ever give. Your Grace.

462
00:41:31.573 --> 00:41:35.118
Ever since my name was read
by the archmaesters at the Great Council.

463
00:41:35.202 --> 00:41:38.580
I have felt Corlys Velaryon's
envious gaze staring at me

464
00:41:38.664 --> 00:41:40.207
from across the Blackwater.

465
00:41:41.166 --> 00:41:44.586
You sit upon the highest seat
in the realm. Your Grace.

466
00:41:44.670 --> 00:41:47.005
Proud men don't like having to look up.

467
00:41:51.009 --> 00:41:52.970
Laena Velaryon.

468
00:41:54.388 --> 00:41:57.766
Lord Corlys is your Master of Ships

469
00:41:57.849 --> 00:42:01.645
and she is the eldest daughter
of the wealthiest house in the realm.

470
00:42:01.728 --> 00:42:05.482
She comes from
unimpeachable Valyrian stock

471
00:42:05.565 --> 00:42:08.193
and she has Targaryen blood.

472
00:42:08.277 --> 00:42:11.154
-What's to mislike?
-She is 12.

473
00:42:11.238 --> 00:42:12.781
She will mature.

474
00:42:15.325 --> 00:42:16.910
I never asked to remarry.

475
00:42:17.619 --> 00:42:20.747
As King. you have a claim on all things.

476
00:42:21.707 --> 00:42:23.166
Even those you don't want.

477
00:42:23.250 --> 00:42:26.253
Marriage is not an obligation
you can put off for long.

478
00:42:26.336 --> 00:42:28.964
What if I was to reject
Lord Corlys's proposal?

479
00:42:29.047 --> 00:42:31.300
He would not be like to take it well.

480
00:42:31.883 --> 00:42:35.679
I fear nothing short of a direct line
to the Iron Throne would satisfy him.

481
00:42:36.513 --> 00:42:39.224
You should also consider
that we find ourselves

482
00:42:39.308 --> 00:42:41.393
on the precipice of war in the Stepstones.

483
00:42:42.436 --> 00:42:45.355
And the Sea Snake holds claim to nearly
half the realm's ships.

484
00:42:45.439 --> 00:42:48.483
He would not dare withhold them
in the face of the realm's need.

485
00:42:49.901 --> 00:42:53.238
-Who is he to hector me?
-No one. Your Grace.

486
00:42:54.823 --> 00:42:58.827
But Driftmark makes for a better ally
than it does an enemy.

487
00:43:00.203 --> 00:43:02.497
The Sea Snake has made a calculated reach.

488
00:43:02.581 --> 00:43:04.708
a fair play for a man of his position.

489
00:43:07.169 --> 00:43:09.546
If you truly want my unencumbered opinion.

490
00:43:09.629 --> 00:43:10.630
I do.

491
00:43:12.049 --> 00:43:14.176
You should wed Laena Velaryon. Your Grace.

492
00:43:15.302 --> 00:43:18.764
Sate Lord Corlys and fix him at your side.

493
00:43:18.847 --> 00:43:20.682
permanently. as an ally.

494
00:43:25.437 --> 00:43:26.813
Your Grace.

495
00:43:26.897 --> 00:43:29.900
the Princess has returned
from Dragonstone.

496
00:43:29.983 --> 00:43:31.651
Dragonstone?

497
00:43:51.630 --> 00:43:52.756
Your Grace.

498
00:43:56.760 --> 00:43:58.929
You disobeyed me.

499
00:43:59.012 --> 00:44:03.016
You fled King's Landing without a word

500
00:44:03.100 --> 00:44:06.645
and you acted without The Crown's leave.

501
00:44:09.815 --> 00:44:11.983
You are my only heir.

502
00:44:13.235 --> 00:44:15.153
You could've been killed.

503
00:44:18.782 --> 00:44:20.158
May I sit?

504
00:44:31.628 --> 00:44:33.922
You went to Dragonstone.

505
00:44:34.005 --> 00:44:36.049
And retrieved the egg without bloodshed.

506
00:44:38.385 --> 00:44:41.513
A feat I'm not sure Ser Otto
could've accomplished alone.

507
00:44:44.641 --> 00:44:46.518
Yes. well.

508
00:44:51.356 --> 00:44:53.900
I sometimes forget
how alike you both were.

509
00:45:04.286 --> 00:45:08.457
Your mother's absence
is a wound that will never heal.

510
00:45:09.875 --> 00:45:11.209
Without her.

511
00:45:11.960 --> 00:45:16.465
the Red Keep has lost a warmth
that I dare say it will never recover.

512
00:45:16.548 --> 00:45:19.676
It pleases me to hear you say this.

513
00:45:23.889 --> 00:45:27.184
To know that I'm not alone in my grief.

514
00:45:27.267 --> 00:45:29.686
I wish I had known better

515
00:45:29.769 --> 00:45:31.980
what to say to you in the aftermath.

516
00:45:34.441 --> 00:45:38.361
I struggled to realize that my daughter
had so quickly become a woman grown.

517
00:45:42.449 --> 00:45:43.992
But I know

518
00:45:44.701 --> 00:45:48.330
she understands
what is now expected of me.

519
00:45:48.413 --> 00:45:50.832
The King must take a new wife.

520
00:45:56.004 --> 00:45:58.131
I could never replace your mother.

521
00:46:00.425 --> 00:46:02.677
No more than I intend
to replace you as heir.

522
00:46:04.513 --> 00:46:06.681
But you are my only heir

523
00:46:06.765 --> 00:46:09.935
and our line is vulnerable.
too easily ended.

524
00:46:11.061 --> 00:46:13.146
And by marrying again.
I may begin to ensure

525
00:46:13.230 --> 00:46:14.773
that we are better defended.

526
00:46:14.856 --> 00:46:15.941
Against whom?

527
00:46:16.024 --> 00:46:18.151
Whomever may dare to challenge us.

528
00:46:24.866 --> 00:46:27.410
I do not wish to make us estranged.

529
00:46:28.328 --> 00:46:29.746
You are the King.

530
00:46:30.330 --> 00:46:33.917
and so. your first duty is to the realm.

531
00:46:37.003 --> 00:46:38.922
Mother would've understood this.

532
00:46:41.633 --> 00:46:43.176
Just as I do.

533
00:47:30.140 --> 00:47:32.058
Good morrow. my lords.

534
00:47:43.320 --> 00:47:46.865
I have decided to take a new wife.

535
00:48:05.300 --> 00:48:06.968
I intend to marry

536
00:48:13.642 --> 00:48:15.769
the Lady Alicent Hightower

537
00:48:17.729 --> 00:48:19.648
before spring's end.

538
00:48:26.446 --> 00:48:28.031
This is an absurdity.

539
00:48:29.199 --> 00:48:31.993
My house is Valyrian.

540
00:48:32.077 --> 00:48:34.204
the greatest power in the realm.

541
00:48:35.580 --> 00:48:37.499
And I am your King.

542
00:49:02.023 --> 00:49:03.566
Rhaenyra.

543
00:49:25.964 --> 00:49:29.509
House Velaryon's origins
reach back to Old Valyria.

544
00:49:31.594 --> 00:49:34.139
More ancient even than House Targaryen

545
00:49:36.099 --> 00:49:38.017
according to some texts.

546
00:49:39.519 --> 00:49:42.105
But unlike the Targaryens.

547
00:49:42.188 --> 00:49:44.107
we were no dragonlords.

548
00:49:45.734 --> 00:49:50.029
For centuries. my house had to scratch out
an existence from the sea

549
00:49:50.113 --> 00:49:52.657
with grit and luck.

550
00:49:54.951 --> 00:49:57.287
When I ascended the Driftwood Throne.

551
00:49:58.538 --> 00:50:00.081
I knew what I wanted.

552
00:50:02.167 --> 00:50:04.085
So I went out and seized it.

553
00:50:05.754 --> 00:50:07.130
Unlike every other lord of the realm.

554
00:50:07.213 --> 00:50:10.258
I can say that I built
my house's high seat

555
00:50:10.341 --> 00:50:12.469
with the strength of mine own back.

556
00:50:19.100 --> 00:50:21.770
I've always thought of
you and I as having been

557
00:50:21.853 --> 00:50:23.605
made from the same cloth.

558
00:50:32.614 --> 00:50:35.450
I wasn't aware you had
a king for a brother.

559
00:50:35.533 --> 00:50:38.953
We're both men who have had to cut
our own way through the world.

560
00:50:39.913 --> 00:50:42.832
We've been passed over too often.

561
00:50:45.710 --> 00:50:46.920
Did you call me to Driftmark

562
00:50:47.003 --> 00:50:49.380
to remind me of my
low standing. Lord Corlys.

563
00:50:49.464 --> 00:50:51.382
or was there some other reason?

564
00:50:55.220 --> 00:50:57.347
You've heard of the troubles
in the Stepstones?

565
00:51:00.558 --> 00:51:04.604
Some Myrish Prince
is feeding Westerosi sailors to the crabs.

566
00:51:04.687 --> 00:51:07.357
I have been petitioning
the King to send my navy

567
00:51:07.440 --> 00:51:09.150
into the territory.

568
00:51:09.234 --> 00:51:11.152
but he's denied me.

569
00:51:11.236 --> 00:51:13.655
It was never my brother's strongest trait.

570
00:51:13.738 --> 00:51:14.697
What?

571
00:51:16.241 --> 00:51:17.659
Being King.

572
00:51:22.163 --> 00:51:24.541
The Crabfeeder is backed
by powerful entities

573
00:51:24.624 --> 00:51:28.169
within the Free Cities who wish to see
Westeros weakened.

574
00:51:30.338 --> 00:51:33.925
And the King's failures
have allowed him to accumulate strength.

575
00:51:35.802 --> 00:51:38.763
If those shipping lanes fall.

576
00:51:38.847 --> 00:51:40.765
my house will be crippled.

577
00:51:41.683 --> 00:51:43.977
And I will not have Driftmark
beggared while our King

578
00:51:44.060 --> 00:51:47.564
idles himself with feasts.
and balls. and tourneys.

579
00:51:47.647 --> 00:51:50.567
I will speak of my brother as I wish.

580
00:51:52.527 --> 00:51:54.028
You will not.

581
00:51:57.448 --> 00:51:59.242
Waiting in the Stepstones

582
00:51:59.325 --> 00:52:01.452
is a chance for you to prove your worth

583
00:52:01.536 --> 00:52:03.830
to any who might yet doubt it.

584
00:52:05.540 --> 00:52:08.084
We are the realm's second sons. Daemon.

585
00:52:09.627 --> 00:52:11.546
Our worth is not given.

586
00:52:13.172 --> 00:52:15.091
It must be made.

586
